Write the taxonomy enum constants and sealed event catalog for this feature.

Taxonomy constants — follow the pattern in `MessagingAnalyticsConstants.kt`. Each enum implements the corresponding illuminate interface:

```kotlin
enum class [Feature]EventType(override val value: String) : EventType { /* one value per event */ }
enum class [Feature]TriggerLocation(override val value: String) : TriggerLocation { ... }
enum class [Feature]TriggerSource(override val value: String) : TriggerSource { ... }
enum class [Feature]TriggerObject(override val value: String) : TriggerObject { ... }
enum class [Feature]SemanticEvent(override val value: String) : SemanticEvent { ... }
```

Sealed event catalog — each `data object` carries a pre-built `ZgIlluminateAnalyticsModel` using the enum constants above:

```kotlin
sealed interface [Feature]AnalyticsEvents {
    val analytics: ZgIlluminateAnalyticsModel
    sealed interface PageView : [Feature]AnalyticsEvents { ... }
    sealed interface Interaction : [Feature]AnalyticsEvents { ... }
    sealed interface Impression : [Feature]AnalyticsEvents { ... }
}
```

If events require contextual data beyond the base model (conversation ID, unread count, etc.), create `[Feature]ContextualData` implementing `ZgIlluminateContextualData` with the required fields.

For each entry in `events`, write a corresponding enum value in `[Feature]EventType`. Never use raw string literals for event type IDs — always go through the enum constants.

Define the telemetry event and error types for this feature.

Create `[Feature]Telemetry.kt` following the pattern in `features/messaging/impl/src/main/java/com/zillow/android/messaging/impl/telemetry/MessagingTelemetry.kt`.

The structure is an `object` containing nested sealed interfaces that extend `ZgIlluminateTelemetryType`:

```kotlin
object [Feature]Telemetry {
    sealed interface Event : ZgIlluminateTelemetryType.Event {
        // No-arg milestone events use data object
        data object RenderCompleted : Event
        // Events with context use data class
        data class SubmitAttempted(val itemCount: Int) : Event
    }
    sealed interface Error : ZgIlluminateTelemetryType.Error {
        // Error subtypes must provide throwable
        data class LoadFailed(override val throwable: Throwable) : Error
    }
}
```

Only add an `Error` block if `telemetryEventsNeeded` includes error-type signals. Only add `Event` subtypes for event/transaction signals.

If Datadog attribution keys are needed (for dashboard filtering), also create:
- `[Feature]TelemetryEventType.kt` — `enum class ... (override val value: String) : ZgIlluminateTelemetryEventType`
- `[Feature]TelemetryErrorType.kt` — `enum class ... (override val value: String) : ZgIlluminateTelemetryErrorType`

Following `MessagingTelemetryEventType.kt` and `MessagingTelemetryErrorType.kt` in the same telemetry directory. These are optional unless the team requires them for Datadog filtering.
